node.title: Tropical Cyclone Seth forms off Queensland coast, large swells expected over weekend
node.alt: A generic image of a Rapid Antigen Test packet, a swab, a small dropper bottle, and the test itself laid out on a blue surface.
node.description: Tropical Cyclone Seth forms in the Coral Sea, north-east of Mackay, with large waves expected along the south-east Queensland coastline over the weekend.
node.content: ["Tropical Cyclone Seth has formed in the Coral Sea\u00a0north-east of Mackay and is\u00a0expected to bring large swells to the south-east Queensland coastline over the weekend.", "The category one\u00a0cyclone is not expected to cross the coast but the Bureau of Meteorology has forecast large waves from tomorrow and through to early next week.", "Cyclone Seth is currently sitting about 495 kilometres east north-east of Mackay and 490 kilometres north-east of Yeppoon with wind gusts of up to 110 kilometres per hour.", "The system is expected to move away from the coast today and into Saturday before taking a southerly track on Sunday where it may intensify into a category two system.", "By Monday Tropical Cyclone Seth\u00a0may move closer to the coast but should\u00a0weaken\u00a0into a sub-tropical low.", "It is currently moving\u00a0about 27 kilometres per hour."]
